      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is highly unlikely that your thermostat and fridge are directly sensing your emotional state. These devices typically rely on standard environmental sensors like temperature and motion. The fluctuations you are noticing could potentially be correlated with subtle changes in your environment when you are stressed, such as changes in body heat or adjacent devices drawing more power. If the behavior persists, please check the wiring and connectivity of both devices with a professional technician.",
